dmenu2 - dynamic menu extended
==============================
dmenu2 is the fork of original dmenu - an efficient dynamic menu for X.
Features implemented:
- xft 
- quiet startup
- x & y offset
- token search
- follow focus
- tab nav
- filter
- vertical menu
- line height
- screen selection on multihead
- window class and name setting
- dmenu opacity
- dim screen while running dmenu by selected opacity level and color
- get image from parsed line and show it in dmenu (vertical only)

Requirements
------------
In order to build dmenu2 you need the Xlib header files, and Imlib.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (dmenu2 is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install dmenu2
(if necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running dmenu2
-------------
See the man page for details.
